	     Johannesburg - Thembisile Yende's murder accused, David Ngwenya has been denied bail at the Springs Magistrate's Court in the east of Johannesburg on Thursday afternoon. Ngwenya (43) - a technician at Eskom - allegedly murdered his lover, Yende, after he suspected that she would "spill the beans" on his involvement in a copper cable theft syndicate. READ: Thembisile Yende murder accused consulted sangoma for 'cloak of invisibility' Yende's body was found 10 days after her disappearance at an isolated Eskom substation and was staged to look like a suicide. He is due to appear in court again on July 17. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  